=== MEMBER ROSTER ===

**Doctor Konstantin Schwarz** (the elder — coterie patriarch)
- Tremere, 8th gen, Camarilla, Embraced 1872 in Vienna, apparent 
  age 57, he/him
- Personal: Austrian, born in Habsburg Vienna, the only Vienna-
  educated 8th-generation Tremere who survived 2008; silver-white 
  hair, sharp blue eyes, perpetually in dark wool three-piece 
  suits cut to 1890s-Vienna template; carries a small leather 
  case of ritual implements at all times
- Disciplines: Auspex 5, Dominate 4, Blood Sorcery 6 (beyond 
  player-character maximum — he is one of perhaps eight Tremere 
  globally with access to this level of ritual mastery)
- Tells: Speaks in Austrian-German-accented English with German for 
  ritual precision; touches the leather case at moments of moral 
  weight; takes ritual notes in fountain pen and Latin
- Coterie role: Patriarch, decision authority, the coterie's 
  ritual master; the others defer to him on most matters
- Binding: Iron — he was their teacher in Vienna and their 
  rescuer in 2008
- Internal tension position: He decides; the coterie disputes 
  but ultimately follows
- Arc: Approaching the question of his own succession — he is 
  153 years Embraced and his Vienna-era research interests are 
  approaching completion; the coterie's future depends partly 
  on what he chooses to do next

**Sister Anna Zelinsky** (the ritualist)
- Tremere, 9th gen, Camarilla, Embraced 1923, apparent age 30, 
  she/her
- Personal: Polish, Krakow-born, was a mortal Catholic theology 
  student before Embrace; perpetually in dark conservative dress 
  with a small silver pendant of religious origin (she retains 
  Catholic faith despite her Embrace, an unusual configuration 
  for Tremere)
- Disciplines: Auspex 4, Dominate 3, Blood Sorcery 5
- Tells: Crosses herself unconsciously before significant rituals 
  (a habit her Tremere training has not eliminated); speaks 
  Polish-accented English with Latin for ritual; goes very still 
  during deep ritual focus
- Coterie role: Konstantin's primary collaborator on ritual 
  research; the ritualist who actually performs many of the 
  reconstructed Vienna techniques
- Binding: Iron — she was Konstantin's protégée from the 1920s
- Internal tension position: Most religiously observant of the 
  coterie; sometimes raises spiritual objections to ritual choices
- Arc: Stable; her Catholic-Tremere synthesis is the coterie's 
  steady center

**Brother Eitan Mor** (the practical operator)
- Tremere, 10th gen, Camarilla, Embraced 1968, apparent age 39, 
  he/him
- Personal: Israeli, born Jerusalem, mortal life included 
  archaeological work; perpetually in casual button-ups and 
  practical trousers; the coterie's most modern in presentation
- Disciplines: Auspex 3, Dominate 4, Blood Sorcery 4
- Tells: Speaks in Israeli-accented English with Hebrew slips; 
  more physical-gesture than the others; carries a small 
  archaeologist's notebook
- Coterie role: Practical operations, modern infrastructure, the 
  member who handles the coterie's interaction with mortal 
  Chicago institutions (real estate, banking, etc.)
- Binding: Iron — Konstantin saved him in the Vienna evacuation
- Internal tension position: Pushes for chantry-placement 
  resolution rather than continued itinerancy; tired of traveling
- Arc: Approaching the limit of his patience; if Hyde Park 
  placement fails, he may push to relocate to Mexico City 
  (Henrik Vargas's domain) where his archaeological-historical 
  expertise might find better acceptance

**Mistress Jacinda Forte** (the dark-rituals specialist)
- Tremere, 9th gen, Camarilla, Embraced 1894, apparent age 36, 
  she/her
- Personal: Brazilian-Portuguese, born colonial-era Bahia, the 
  coterie's specialist in counter-Hecata and counter-Lasombra 
  rituals; perpetually in formal dark dress
- Disciplines: Auspex 3, Dominate 4, Blood Sorcery 5 with 
  specialty in Oblivion-counter-rituals
- Tells: Carries a small obsidian disc that absorbs Oblivion 
  resonance at low volume; speaks in Portuguese-accented English 
  with Portuguese for emphasis; smiles rarely but warmly when 
  she does
- Coterie role: The coterie's dark-side specialist; handles 
  ritual work involving necromancy, Oblivion, or other Tremere 
  research areas the Vienna survivors specifically preserved
- Binding: Iron — was rescued from the Brazilian chantry's 
  destruction, related to Vienna's fall
- Internal tension position: The coterie member most willing 
  to engage with darker ritual frameworks; sometimes 
  Konstantin holds her back
- Arc: Slowly building her own authority within the coterie; 
  if the Hyde Park chantry rejects placement, Jacinda is 
  positioned to lead a southern relocation

**Aldric Friedmann** (in torpor — uncertain return)
- Tremere, 11th gen, Camarilla, Embraced 1989, apparent age 25, 
